The paper deals with the Metric Path Traveling Salesman Problem, which is a problem in combinatorial optimization. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve dynamic programming and exploiting the structure of cuts in graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves approximation algorithms and graph theory, which make cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely sub-categories as well.
